-- 2012-08-10T09:23:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-10/ntpc-seeks-400-000-tons-of-imported-coal-for-simhadri-plant.html
NTPC Ltd. is seeking 400,000 metric
tons of thermal coal for a power plant in the south Indian state
of Andhra Pradesh, according to a document on its  website .  The company,  India â€™s biggest power producer, is seeking
coal with 5,000 kilocalories per kilogram on an as-received
basis, total moisture of 30 percent, ash of 8 percent and sulfur
of 0.6 percent to be delivered at NTPC Simhadri in a six-month
period starting September 2012, according to the document. The
tender closes Aug. 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
